<h1>Instructions:</h1>

<p>You must have ruby1.8 installed in your machine. Then, put the .rb files in a folder and add that to your path, <br />
or even add the .rb files to your VHDL project folder. To refactor the VHDL when an entity changes, run: <br /> </p>
<p>
	<b>ruby vhdl-reentity entity</b>
</p>
